django setup
==============================

> install pyhton
> install pip

> install django
pip3 install django version
sudo apt install python3-django
> to chcek django version
django-admin --version

> to uninstall django
sudo/sudo pip  unintstall django

> to activate virtual env
source project/venv/bin/activate
> to deactivate virtual env
deactivate 

> to start a django project
django-admin startproject projceName

> to run django server
python manage.py runserver

> to create a new app
python manage.py startapp appName

> to add migrations after building a model
python manage.py makemigrations

> to reflect models into databse
python manage.py migrate

**pyMySQL is not needed for django 2.2

> pip install pyMySQL
> pip install mysql-python
> sudo apt-get install python3-dev
> pip install configparser
> sudo apt-get install mysql-server
> sudo apt-get install python libmysqlclient-dev

> to install mysql client(for django 2.2)
sudo apt-get install mysqlclient
